## RLS Policies

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Identity standard**: All policies use `auth.uid()` directly — no `get_current_profile_id()`. Since `profiles.id = auth.uid()`, FKs like `uploader_profile_id` and `profile_id` can be compared to `auth.uid()` directly.

### `inspiration_items`

| Op | Policy Type | Rule |
|---|---|---|
| **SELECT** | `USING` | `(state='published' AND visibility='public')` OR `uploader_profile_id = auth.uid()` OR `is_admin()` |
| **INSERT** (user) | `WITH CHECK` | `uploader_profile_id = auth.uid() AND state = 'pending_review' AND visibility = 'private'` |
| **INSERT** (admin) | `WITH CHECK` | `is_admin()` (no state/visibility restriction) |
| **UPDATE** (user) | `USING` | `uploader_profile_id = auth.uid() AND state IN ('draft','pending_review')` |
| **UPDATE** (user) | `WITH CHECK` | `state IN ('draft','pending_review') AND visibility = 'private'` |
| **UPDATE** (admin) | `USING` + `WITH CHECK` | `is_admin()` |
| **DELETE** | `USING` | `is_admin()` only |

### `categories`, `tags`, `item_categories`, `item_tags`
| Op | Rule |
|---|---|
| SELECT | Public (anyone, including anon) |
| INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE | `is_admin()` |

### `favorites`
| Op | Rule |
|---|---|
| SELECT / INSERT / DELETE | `profile_id = auth.uid()` |

### `admin_action_log`
| Op | Rule |
|---|---|
| SELECT / INSERT | `is_admin()` |

### `delete_requests`
| Op | Rule |
|---|---|
| SELECT | `requester_profile_id = auth.uid()` OR `is_admin()` |
| INSERT | `WITH CHECK`: `requester_profile_id = auth.uid()` |
| UPDATE | `is_admin()` |

